wikipedia_page.main: Frederick David Mocatta (1828–1905) was an English financier and philanthropist, from a notable Anglo-Jewish family,

response: *Frederick David Mocatta (1828–1905), a prominent philanthropist, bibliophile, patron of the arts, and bullion broker

The Jewish Historical Society of England (JHSE) was founded in 1893 by several Anglo-Jewish scholars, including Lucien Wolf, who became the society's first president. Early presidents of the JHSE included Hermann Adler, Michael Adler, Joseph Jacobs, Frederick David Mocatta, and Sir Isidore Spielmann.
* Frederick David Mocatta (1828–1905), British financier and philanthropist
